ATTACHMENT A Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Pleinmont Solar 1, LLC Reactive Power Compensation
PLEINMONT SOLAR 1, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Pleinmont Solar 1, LLC ("Pleinmont 1") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Pleinmont 1 generating facility ("Pleinmont 1 Facility").
The Pleinmont 1 Facility is a solar generating facility located in Spotsylvania County, Virginia. The Pleinmont 1 Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Virginia Electric and Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Pleinmont 1's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Pleinmont 1 Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Pleinmont 1's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Pleinmont 1 shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $1,009,038.34 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $84,086.53
